{"title_page": "Maitighar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n|italic title = yes\n|name     = Maitighar\n|image    = Maitighar.jpg\n|caption  =theatrical released poster Maitighar\n|director = B.S. Thapa\n|producer = Sumononjali Films\n|writer   =B.S. Thapa\n|starring = {{ubl|[[Mala Sinha]]|[[Sunil Dutt]]|[[Rajendra Nath]]}}\n|music    = [[Jaidev]]\n|released = {{Film date|1966|12|16|df=y}}\n| runtime = 134 minutes\n|country  = [[Nepal]]\n|language = [[Nepali language|Nepali]]\n}}\n\n'''Maitighar''' ({{Translation}} Maternal home) is a 1966 Nepali film directed by B.S. Thapa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmnepal.net/maitighar-1966/|title=Maitighar (1966)|publisher=Filmnepal.net|accessdate=9 March 2012|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120711005938/http://filmnepal.net/maitighar-1966/|archive-date=11 July 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was the third Nepali film produced and the first under a private banner. This film features [[bollywood]] actress [[Mala Sinha]] in the lead role with Nepali actor Chidambar Prasad Lohani whom she marries.\n\n==Plot==\nA girl who was born in [[Pokhara]] was sent to jail for 11 years but she didn't want to go out of the jail then police officer calls a deceive doctor than she tells her story about herself.\n\nShe tells the story falling in love with and marrying Mohan and living a simple life with him. But they get separated from each other when Mohan goes to the jungle for the hunt to kill animals but he comes home dead.\n\nAfter the death of Mohan, his mother calls Maya a witch who killed her son (common superstition at that time in Nepal) and everyone calls her witch and they say \"Wish she died before birth\".\n\nThen she gets blamed for everything that happens in the village and Mohan's mother takes her son away. After that she decides to leave the village than living in a house like a hell. While she was leaving her house people find her then start to chase her down.\n\nThen she finds a woman at a random place who sells her as a dancer and locks her down in her house. She tries to escape that place and when all goes in vain, she tries to kill herself in that room but fails.\n\nAfter while she accepts her job but she wishes to see her son \"Ratu\" but they say you can't see him than she starts to beg to she her son after that they let her see her son\n\nAfter that, she joins a college for speaking she tells everyone about the old Nepal from her religious Hindu book. She gives advice to everyone about living life.\n\nAfter her job at college she gets accused of killing of her owner \"'''Malik Sab'''\" than she gets sentenced to prison for 11 years. Then the story reveals how had killed himself with Bish/Drugs. Then she meets her son at the prison as a police officer.\n\nThan her son and her meet her daughter as last wish of her before going to the prison. After telling the story she kills herself at the prison. After they resized the police officer and her mitini were her children. The films end with her death with a song.\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Mala Sinha]] as Maya - the key cast/role in this movie. She is married to Mohan and was sentenced to 11 years in prison. \n*Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan/Moha \n*Yadav Kharel\n*Tika Bhushan Dahal\n*Yam Bahadur Khadka\n*Sunita Regmi\n*Yadu Kumari\n*Pratibha Sam\n*Jana Darshan Sam\n*Gopi Krishna\n*K.B. Lamichhane\n*Keshab Rana\n*B.S. Thapa \n*Nanda Kishore Timilsina\n*[[Sunil Dutt]] in a special appearance\n*[[Rajendra Nath]] in a special appearance\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Chha Salaam Kasari Bolam\n| length1 = 5:01\n| extra1 = C.P. Lohani\n| title2 = Hansi Kheli Yehi Dhuloma\n| length2 = 4:00\n| extra2 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title3 = Hera Dharti Dagmagai\n| length3 = 5:54\n| extra3 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title4 = Hey Suna Aaja Ma Timi Haru\n| length4 =4:25\n| extra4 = C.P. Lohani\n| title5 = Jai Jai Janani Nepal\n| length5 = 2:07\n| extra5 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title6 = Jun Mato Ma Mero\n| length6 =3:05\n| extra6 =[[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n| title7 = Kala Kurtaile\n| length7 = 5:34\n| extra7 =C.P. Lohani, [[Aruna Lama]]\n| title8 =Ma Pyar Bechidinchu\n| length8 = 4:24\n| extra8 =[[Asha Bhosle]]\n| title9 =Namana Laaj Yestari\n| length9 = 4:06\n| extra9 =[[Prem Dhoj Pradhan]], [[Usha Mangeshkar]]\n| title10 = Salloma Bhanu Sallo Ho\n| length10 = 4:23\n| extra10 =[[Aruna Lama]], [[Geeta Dutt]]\n| title11 =Sanu Maya Mero Maya Lai\n| length11 =1:20\n| extra11 =[[Aruna Lama]], [[Geeta Dutt]]\n| title12 = Tinai Sahar Nepali Ma\n| length12 = 3:40\n| extra12 =C.P. Lohani\n| title13 = Unbhoma Jharne Banko Bato\n| length13 = 5:20\n| extra13 =C.P. Lohani, [[Aruna Lama]]\n| title14 =Yo Ho Mero Pran Bhanda Pyaro Maitighar\n| length14 =5:23\n| extra14 = [[Asha Bhosle]]\n| title15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n| total_length =52:57\n}}\n\nThe music was scored by [[Jaidev]], a veteran music maestro. [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Asha Bhosle]], [[Usha Mangeshkar]], [[Manna Dey]] and [[Geeta Dutt]] did the playback singing, along with Nepali singers [[Prem Dhoj Pradhan]], C.P. Lohani and [[Aruna Lama]]. Lata Mangeshkar sang a Nepali song that was penned by the late King [[Mahendra Bir Bikram Shah Dev]] of Nepal.\n\n== Production ==\n''Maitighar'' was the first film to be produced under a private banner in [[Nepal]]. It had many Indians contributing towards the making of the film - actors, musicians and technicians. The place where the office for film shooting was established in [[Kathmandu]], Nepal has been named Maitighar after the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nepalibeats.blogspot.in/2007/01/maitighar.html|title=Nepali Beats (Maitighar)|publisher=Nepali Beats|accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nMaithighar was a commercially successful movie in Nepal after the success of the movie the place this movie was filmed in got named Maithighar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://filmsofnepal.com/maitighar-1966/|title=Nepali Film \u2013 Maitighar (1966)|date=2009-06-19|work=Films of Nepal|access-date=2017-06-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 1.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan (Moha)\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 2.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan and Mala Sinha as Maya, main protagonist\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 3.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan, son of the village aristocrat\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 4.png|Unknown actor in the song ''Kala Kurtai ley''\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 5.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani with Mala Sinha\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 6.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani with Mala Sinha\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 7.png|Main antagonist of the movie\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 8.png|owner of the harem persuading Maya\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 9.png|a spy of the main antagonist\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 10.png|Rekha, daughter of main protagonist Maya\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 11.png|Mala Sinha as Maya\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://nepalicollections.com/album.php?id=12 Songs of ''Maitighar'']\n* [https://archive.is/20130130103433/http://www.nepalilyrix.com/2012/12/yo-ho-mero-pran-bhanda-pyaro-maitighar.html Maitighar Lyrics]\n* [http://www.netofnepal.com/about/]\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Nepalese films]]\n*[[Cinema of Nepal]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Nepalese films]]\n[[Category:Nepali-language films]]\n[[Category:1966 films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n|italic title = yes\n|name     = Maitighar\n|image    = Maitighar.jpg\n|caption  =theatrical released poster Maitighar\n|director = B.S. Thapa\n|producer = Sumononjali Films\n|writer   =B.S. Thapa\n|starring = {{ubl|[[Mala Sinha]]|[[Sunil Dutt]]|[[Rajendra Nath]]}}\n|music    = [[Jaidev]]\n|released = {{Film date|1966|12|16|df=y}}\n| runtime = 134 minutes\n|country  = [[Nepal]]\n|language = [[Nepali language|Nepali]]\n}}\n\n'''Maitighar''' ({{Translation}} Maternal home) is a 1966 Nepali film directed by B.S. Thapa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmnepal.net/maitighar-1966/|title=Maitighar (1966)|publisher=Filmnepal.net|accessdate=9 March 2012|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120711005938/http://filmnepal.net/maitighar-1966/|archive-date=11 July 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was the third Nepali film produced and the first under a private banner. This film features [[bollywood]] actress [[Mala Sinha]] in the lead role with nepali actor Chidambar Prasad Lohani who she gets married to.\n\n==Plot==\nA girl who was born in [[Pokhara]] was sent to jail for 11 years but she didn't want to go out of the jail then police officer calls a deceive doctor than she tells her story about herself.\n\nShe tells the story falling in love with and marrying Mohan and living a simple life with him. But they get separated from each other when Mohan goes to the jungle for the hunt to kill animals but he comes home dead.\n\nAfter the death of Mohan, his mother calls Maya a witch who killed her son (common superstition at that time in Nepal) and everyone calls her witch and they say \"Wish she died before birth\".\n\nThen she gets blamed for everything that happens in the village and Mohan's mother takes her son away. After that she decides to leave the village than living in a house like a hell. While she was leaving her house people find her then start to chase her down.\n\nThen she finds a woman at a random place who sells her as a dancer and locks her down in her house. She tries to escape that place and when all goes in vain, she tries to kill herself in that room but fails.\n\nAfter while she accepts her job but she wishes to see her son \"Ratu\" but they say you can't see him than she starts to beg to she her son after that they let her see her son\n\nAfter that, she joins a college for speaking she tells everyone about the old Nepal from her religious Hindu book. She gives advice to everyone about living life.\n\nAfter her job at college she gets accused of killing of her owner \"'''Malik Sab'''\" than she gets sentenced to prison for 11 years. Then the story reveals how had killed himself with Bish/Drugs. Then she meets her son at the prison as a police officer.\n\nThan her son and her meet her daughter as last wish of her before going to the prison. After telling the story she kills herself at the prison. After they resized the police officer and her mitini were her children. The films end with her death with a song.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Mala Sinha]] as Maya - the key cast/role in this movie. She is married to Mohan and got prison sentences for 11 years. \n* Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan/Moha \n*Yadav Kharel as \n*Tika Bhushan Dahal\n*Yam Bahadur Khadka\n*Sunita Regmi\n*Yadu Kumari\n*Pratibha Sam\n*Jana Darshan Sam\n*Gopi Krishna\n*K.B. Lamichhane\n*Keshab Rana\n*B.S. Thapa \n*Nanda Kishore Timilsina\n* [[Sunil Dutt]] in a special appearance\n* [[Rajendra Nath]] in a special appearance\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Chha Salaam Kasari Bolam\n| length1 = 5:01\n| extra1 = C.P. Lohani\n| title2 = Hansi Kheli Yehi Dhuloma\n| length2 = 4:00\n| extra2 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title3 = Hera Dharti Dagmagai\n| length3 = 5:54\n| extra3 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title4 = Hey Suna Aaja Ma Timi Haru\n| length4 =4:25\n| extra4 = C.P. Lohani\n| title5 = Jai Jai Janani Nepal\n| length5 = 2:07\n| extra5 = [[Manna Dey]]\n| title6 = Jun Mato Ma Mero\n| length6 =3:05\n| extra6 =[[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n| title7 = Kala Kurtaile\n| length7 = 5:34\n| extra7 =C.P. Lohani, [[Aruna Lama]]\n| title8 =Ma Pyar Bechidinchu\n| length8 = 4:24\n| extra8 =[[Asha Bhosle]]\n| title9 =Namana Laaj Yestari\n| length9 = 4:06\n| extra9 =[[Prem Dhoj Pradhan]], [[Usha Mangeshkar]]\n| title10 = Salloma Bhanu Sallo Ho\n| length10 = 4:23\n| extra10 =[[Aruna Lama]], [[Geeta Dutt]]\n| title11 =Sanu Maya Mero Maya Lai\n| length11 =1:20\n| extra11 =[[Aruna Lama]], [[Geeta Dutt]]\n| title12 = Tinai Sahar Nepali Ma\n| length12 = 3:40\n| extra12 =C.P. Lohani\n| title13 = Unbhoma Jharne Banko Bato\n| length13 = 5:20\n| extra13 =C.P. Lohani, [[Aruna Lama]]\n| title14 =Yo Ho Mero Pran Bhanda Pyaro Maitighar\n| length14 =5:23\n| extra14 = [[Asha Bhosle]]\n| title15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n| total_length =52:57\n}}\n\nThe music was scored by [[Jaidev]], a veteran music maestro. [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Asha Bhosle]], [[Usha Mangeshkar]], [[Manna Dey]] and [[Geeta Dutt]] did the playback singing, along with Nepali singers [[Prem Dhoj Pradhan]], C.P. Lohani and [[Aruna Lama]]. Lata Mangeshkar sang a Nepali song that was penned by the late King [[Mahendra Bir Bikram Shah Dev]] of Nepal.\n\n== Production ==\n''Maitighar'' was the first film to be produced under a private banner in [[Nepal]]. It had many Indians contributing towards the making of the film - actors, musicians and technicians. The place where the office for film shooting was established in [[Kathmandu]], Nepal has been named Maitighar after the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nepalibeats.blogspot.in/2007/01/maitighar.html|title=Nepali Beats (Maitighar)|publisher=Nepali Beats|accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nMaithighar was a commercially successful movie in Nepal after the success of the movie the place this movie was filmed in got named Maithighar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://filmsofnepal.com/maitighar-1966/|title=Nepali Film \u2013 Maitighar (1966)|date=2009-06-19|work=Films of Nepal|access-date=2017-06-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 1.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan (Moha)\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 2.png|Chidambar Prasad Lohani as Mohan and Mala Sinha as Maya, main protagonist\nFile:Maitighar screenshot 3.png